15 The Federal Register's Archives Go Digital 
Nextgov: The Federal Register is moving 1.8 million pages -- covering government regulations from the era of the New Deal to Bill Clinton's first term -- into cyberspace.The Federal Register and the Government Publishing Office have recently joined forces to digitize the registerâ€™s documents created between 1936 and 1994. They plan to complete the project by next year.
